-----------Names-----------
Names: Jingyu Oh (cs184-da), Richard Jiang (cs184-ce)

-----------Platform----------- 
Mac OSX Yosemite (with make), Windows (Visual Studio Pro 2012), Instructional Machines

-----------Source Code-----------
Submitted by cs184-da (Jingyu Oh) as zip hw3. 
C++ code + binaries with GLUT library (folder glut-3.7.6), using OPENGL

-----------How To Use (MAKE)-----------
To run:
1. “make”
2. “./as3 (args)”

If you get an error “Inconsistency detected by ld.so” simply run with “LD_PRELOAD=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/mesa/libGL.so.1 ./as1 (args)” - this is a graphic driver issue (post 80 on piazza). 

To clean (optional):
1. "make clean"

-----------How To Use (VISUAL STUDIO)-----------
Put file into Visual Studio and it should run. 

-----------Site-----------
Our hw3 site is located at: http://inst.cs.berkeley.edu/~CS184-da/hw3/hw3.html and has prettier pictures and stuff. 

-----------Features (Arguments/Input)-----------
The format of our arguments is:
"./as3 [inputfile.bez] [param] [-a]"

A sample call would be:
"./as3 test.bez 0.1 -a"

----MANDATORY(required)-----

-Read in a .bez file ([inputfile.bez])

-Parse param (see below)

-Enable adaptive subdivision [-a]
if turned on, param becomes the maximum error to allow without splitting triangle in adaptive subdivision
else, this becomes subdivision step param

-Toggle flat/smooth shading
Press "s"

-Toggle filled/wireframe mode
Press "w"

-Rotate view around object
Press arrow keys

-Translate view around object
Press shift + arrow keys

-Zoom in/out
Press +/- keys









